Huawei’s latest flagship smartphone range is now available from Technomobi. You can pre-order the Huawei P20, Huawei P20 Pro, and Huawei P20 Lite from Technomobi here. The online retailer stated that once your pre-order is booked, the P20 Lite and P20 will ship from 4 April 2018. The Huawei P20 Pro is set to be available from 9 April. Prices for the new smartphone start at R5,999 – making it an affordable flagship for users who demand style and performance. Technomobi stated that all deals also offer the first 100 customers a free Huawei SoundStone Portable Bluetooth speaker. Technomobi’s Huawei P20 range is priced as follows. The new Huawei smartphones are also available on contract from Vodacom. Technomobi highlighted the following contract deals for the Huawei P20 from the online retailer. Huawei P20 Lite Huawei P20 Huawei P20 Pro The Huawei P20 features a Leica dual-camera on the rear – packing 12MP and 20MP sensors – and a 24MP front camera. For the display, Huawei has packed a 5.8-inch Fullview screen into the device, which is powered by a Kirin 970 chipset, 3,400mAh battery, and 4GB of RAM. The Huawei P20 Pro packs a 6.1-inch display, 4,000mAh battery, 6GB of RAM, and 128GB of storage.    This article was published in partnership with Technomobi.